# SewMumbai — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Monorepo: `client/` (Vite + React) + `server/` (Express + Mongoose)
- Client: React 18, React Router, Axios, Tailwind CSS, Google Fonts (Outfit + Fraunces)
- Server: Node.js ES modules, Express, Mongoose, JWT (jsonwebtoken), bcryptjs, express-validator, cors, dotenv
- Database: MongoDB

## Architecture
- Keep API under `/api` prefix; Vite proxies `/api` → `http://localhost:5000`
- Auth: JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>`; roles: `customer` | `tailor` | `admin`
- Tailors and services require admin approval before public visibility
- Bookings: customer requests → tailor accept/reject → complete → customer review (one per booking)
- Mumbai locality-based search only — use `server/src/constants/localities.js`
- Mobile-first UI; brand navy `#0B1D36` + saffron `#E07A3D`; fonts Outfit (UI) + Fraunces (display)
- Avoid purple gradients, Inter/Roboto/Arial defaults, cream+terracotta newspaper layouts

## Constraints
- Do not invent endpoints outside the documented API surface without updating README
- Hash passwords with bcrypt; never commit real secrets — use `.env.example`
- Validate inputs at route boundaries with express-validator
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones unless a clear module boundary requires it
- Keep files under ~500 lines; split controllers/routes when growing
